      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">0.99</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">論語 4.2</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">Analects II.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>子曰：「不仁者，不可以久處約，不可以長處樂。仁者安仁，知者利仁。」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The Master said, "Those who are without virtue cannot abide long either in a condition of poverty and hardship, or in a condition of enjoyment. The virtuous rest in virtue; the wise desire virtue."</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="lunyu__book-04-liren__003__zhwikisource-20260529__legge-cc-v1-1893">
