      <prop type="x-translation-ref">Analects XV.15</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>子曰：「參乎！吾道一以貫之。」曾子曰：「唯。」子出，門人問曰：「何謂也？」曾子曰：「夫子之道，忠恕而已矣！」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The Master said, "Shan, my doctrine is that of an all-pervading unity." The disciple Tsang replied, "Yes." The Master went out, and the other disciples asked, saying, "What do his words mean?" Tsang said, "The doctrine of our master is to be true to the principles of our nature and the benevolent exercise of them to others,—this and nothing more."</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
